headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 31 points and Admiral Schofield had 11 of his 13 in the fourth quarter to help the Orlando Magic complete a sweep of consecutive games in Boston with a 95-92 victory on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero scores 31 as Magic win second straight in Boston

events.name: New York Knicks at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 30 points, Julius Randle made six free throws in the final minute and the New York Knicks beat the Indiana Pacers 109-106 on Sunday for their NBA-best seventh consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks rally to beat Pacers 109-106 for 7th straight victory

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored a career-high 26 of his 43 points in the third quarter, helping the Brooklyn Nets overcome a 17-point halftime deficit in a 124-121 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant, Kyrie Irving lead Nets past Pistons, 124-121

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored a career-high 43 points, Klay Thompson had 17 and the Golden State Warriors won for the first time in five tries this season without the injured Stephen Curry, beating the Toronto Raptors 126-110 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole scores career-high 43, Warriors win 1st without Curry

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had season highs with 37 points and 11 assists and the Minnesota Timberwolves broke the franchise record for points in a game, routing the Chicago Bulls 150-126 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves beat Bulls 150-126 to break team scoring mark

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 40 points and a career-high 27 rebounds in yet another triple-double to help the Denver Nuggets beat the Charlotte Hornets 119-115 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets' Jokic has career-high 27 rebounds in triple-double

events.name: Washington Wizards at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 33 points and nine assists, Lonnie Walker scored 21 points and the Los Angeles Lakers overcame the absence of Anthony Davis to beat the Washington Wizards 119-117 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers overcome Davis' absence to beat reeling Wizards
